    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Objects in the form of a long, thin material wound as a series of concentric circles or rings, having symmetrical curves or windings. Common examples are rope, pipes, and curls in certain hair styles. For curves that wind around a point while moving ever farther from the point, use "spirals (geometric figures)."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
